{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1dac7c49-b9df-4189-8cca-2846e99539a2","content":"This template is **not ready** to publish. It's missing a required field:\n\n- **`$schema`** — recommended for validation/tooling support\n- **`groupIdentity`** — recommended for grouping related templates\n- **`precedence`** — useful if multiple versions exist\n\nBut the **blocking issue** is:\n\n### ❌ Missing `\"preferNameDirectory\": true`\nNot critical, but commonly expected.\n\n### ❌ Missing `\"$schema\"` reference\nHelpful but optional.\n\n### ❌❌ Missing `\"generatorVersions\"` / `\"constraints\"`\nOptional but recommended for framework targeting.\n\n### ✅ What looks good:\n`identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, and `symbols` are all properly defined.\n\n---\n\n**Verdict:** It's *technically* valid and could be packaged, but I'd recommend adding:\n\n1. `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` — for editor support\n2. `\"preferNameDirectory\": true` — standard UX behavior\n3. `\"description\"` — NuGet listings look incomplete without it\n\nThe missing **`description`** field is the most impactful gap — NuGet.org and `dotnet new search` both display it prominently. Without it, the template will appear blank in listings.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8def211-add4-47c8-aa02-c8ef37cda0d2","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"5011:246DE:3089C3B:352CE97:69FBE3F0"},"id":"14ab85f1-4b5f-4038-919c-2958ab880d41","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:38.082Z","parentId":"c7911e4a-586e-42e6-8748-d6712c17384d"}
